compute_region.description: Region to create bastion host in. Can be defined in global data block.

compute_zone.description: Zone to create bastion host in. Can be defined in global data block.

image_family.description: Family of compute image to use.

image_project.description: Project of compute image to use.

members.description: Members who can access the bastion host.

network.description: Name of the bastion host's network.

network_project_id.description: Name of network project. If unset, will use the current project.

scopes.description: Scopes to grant. If unset, will grant access to all cloud platform scopes.

startup_script.description: Script to run on startup. Can be multi-line.

subnet.description: Name of the bastion host's subnet.

access.description:
Access for this bigquery dataset.
              Each object should contain exactly one of the following keys:
              - group_by_email
              - user_by_email
              - special_group

group_by_email.description: An email address of a Google Group to grant access to.

special_group.description: A special group to grant access to.

user_by_email.description: An email address of a user to grant access to.

bigquery_location.description: Location to create the bigquery dataset. Can be defined in global data block.

resource_name.description:
Override for Terraform resource name. If unset, defaults to normalized dataset_id.
              Normalization will make all characters alphanumeric with underscores.

binary_authorization.description: A policy for container image binary authorization.

admission_whitelist_patterns.description: A whitelist of image patterns to exclude from admission rules.

name_pattern.description:
An image name pattern to whitelist, in the form registry/path/to/image.
                  This supports a trailing * as a wildcard, but this is allowed only in text after the registry/ part."

cloud_sql_region.description: Region to create cloud sql instance in. Can be defined in global data block.

cloud_sql_zone.description: Zone to reate cloud sql instance in. Can be defined in global data block.

name.description: Name of the cloud sql instance.

network_project_id.description: Name of network project. If unset, will use the current project.

resource_name.description:
Override for Terraform resource name. If unset, defaults to normalized name.
              Normalization will make all characters alphanumeric with underscores.

type.description: Type of the cloud sql instance. Currently only supports 'mysql'.

disk_size_gb.description: Disk space to set for the instance template.

disk_type.description: Type of disk to use for the instance template.

enable_shielded_vm.description: Whether to enable shielded VM. Defaults to true.

image_family.description: Family of compute image to use.

image_project.description: Project of compute image to use.

name_prefix.description: Name prefix of the instance template.

preemptible.description: Whether the instance template can be preempted. Defaults to false.

resource_name.description:
Override for Terraform resource name. If unset, defaults to normalized name_prefix.

service_account.description: Email of service account to attach to this instance template.

subnet.description: Name of the the instance template's subnet.

cloud_sql_private_service_access.description: Whether to enable Cloud SQL private service access. Defaults to false.

nats.description: NATs to attach to the router.

source_subnetwork_ip_ranges_to_nat.description: How NAT should be configured per Subnetwork.

subnetworks.description: Subnet NAT configurations. Only applicable if 'source_subnetwork_ip_ranges_to_nat' is 'LIST_OF_SUBNETWORKS'.

secondary_ip_range_names.description: List of the secondary ranges of the subnetwork that are allowed to use NAT. Only applicable if one of the values in 'source_ip_ranges_to_nat' is 'LIST_OF_SECONDARY_IP_RANGES'.

source_ip_ranges_to_nat.description: List of options for which source IPs in the subnetwork should have NAT enabled.

network.description: Name of network the router belongs to.

List of master authorized networks. If none are provided, disallow external

lifecycle_rules.description: Lifecycle rules configuration for the bucket.

type.description: Type of action. Supported values: Delete and SetStorageClass.

matches_storage_class.description: Storage Class of objects to satisfy this condition.

num_newer_versions.description: Relevant only for versioned objects. The number of newer versions of an object to satisfy this condition.
